{meta: title Shadows On The Wall}
{meta: artist Jean Shepard}
{meta: composer Tommy Reiff and Ronnie Badger}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Though the door was open wide not a sound came from [F]inside
[G7]So I looked and saw two shadows on the [C]wall
[F]One was new and strange to me one my sweetheart dear to me
[G7]How it hurt to see those shadows on the [C]wall
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[F]They were kissing like true lovers always [C]do
[D7]Right then and there I knew that we were [G7]through
[C]So I turned and walked away broken hearted to this [F]day
[G7]All because of those two shadows on the [C]wall
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]Not a tear came to my eyes I was hurt too much to cry
[G7]By that faithful kiss of shadows on the [C]wall
[F]Now I know the misery of living with the memory
[G7]Of that night I saw those shadows on the [C]wall
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[F]If my heart could only fall for someone [C]new
[D7]But it's afraid to take the chance it's [G7]true
[C]Nothing seems to heal the wound guess that I'm forever [F]doomed
[G7]To be haunted by the shadows on the [C]wall
{end_of_verse}
